Ri referred to a joint statement by Kim Jong-un and Donald Trump, held on June 12 in Singapore at the very first summit between a U.S. president in office and a North Korean leader, when Kim pledged to work in favor of a “denuclearization of the North Korean peninsula to ensure that the North Korean peninsula is safe.
North Korea is seeking to officially end the Korean War (1950-1953), but the United States has said that Pyongyang must first give up its nuclear weapons.
