Despite all this, the tone of Ri’s speech was radically different from last year’s, when he said before the UN General Assembly that it was inevitable to point North Korean missiles on North American territory after the “malicious” President Trump called him “man” Kim.
Trump, who had threatened the United Nations last year to “completely destroy” North Korea, did not pay tribute this year to Kim’s courage to implement disarmament measures, but added that there would still be a lot to be done and that sanctions would not be so decreasing from North Korea.
